-- Poland's Orange and mBank want to create mobile bank services
-- 
-- Wed Mar 19, 2014 03:39PM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, March 19 (Reuters) - The Polish unit of France's Orange <ORAN.PA> will work with mBank <MBK.WA>, a unit of Germany's Commerzbank <CBKG.DE>, to provide mobile financial services, both companies said in a statement on Wednesday.

Orange <OPL.WA> and mBank want to create a mobile retail bank for smartphone and tablet users under the Orange brand in the second half of 2014.